.TH GH\-TO\-GIT\-ISSUE 1 "2026-03-01" "git-issue 1.0.0-rc1" "Git Issue Tracker"
.SH NAME
gh\-to\-git\-issue \- convert GitHub issues to git-issue format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gh issue list \-\-json ... |
.B gh\-to\-git\-issue
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads GitHub issue JSON from standard input (as produced by
.BR "gh issue list \-\-json" )
and writes git-issue\-compatible records to standard output,
suitable for piping into
.BR "git issue import" .
.PP
Requires
.BR jq (1).
.SH FIELD MAPPING
.TS
l l.
GitHub field	git-issue field
_
number	(used for hash ID)
title	title
body	description
state	status (closed\(->closed, *\(->open)
author.login	author
labels	priority (inferred from label names)
createdAt	created
updatedAt	updated
url	(preserved as comment)
.TE
.SH INPUT LIMITS
Title, description, author, and label fields are truncated to
prevent oversized imports.
.SH EXAMPLES
Import all open issues from a GitHub repo:
.PP
.RS
.nf
gh issue list \-\-json number,title,body,state,author,createdAt,updatedAt,url \e
  | gh\-to\-git\-issue \e
  | git issue import
.fi
.RE
